sdp/prd-deniable-asset-bus-2026-05-29.md:1:# Deniable Asset Bus — Producer Side PRD
sdp/prd-deniable-asset-bus-2026-05-29.md:3:**Project:** PromptClaw / Deniable Asset Bus
sdp/prd-deniable-asset-bus-2026-05-29.md:16:music, voiceover, sfx — produced by CypherClaw. The **requester** contract is already
sdp/prd-deniable-asset-bus-2026-05-29.md:18:request file to `requests/<request_id>.json` and polls for `deliverables/<request_id>.result.json`.
sdp/prd-deniable-asset-bus-2026-05-29.md:21:requests, generates assets, and writes deliverables + manifests back. The producer must honor
sdp/prd-deniable-asset-bus-2026-05-29.md:22:the v0.1 contract exactly, hide its own internals from the requester, and degrade honestly when
sdp/prd-deniable-asset-bus-2026-05-29.md:26:this orchestrator live). The producer runs as a laptop-side loop that dispatches the actual
sdp/prd-deniable-asset-bus-2026-05-29.md:36:  (`$DENIABLE_ASSET_BUS` default `~/deniable-asset-bus`, with `requests/`, `deliverables/`,
sdp/prd-deniable-asset-bus-2026-05-29.md:37:  `status/`), the request JSON (`request_id`, `schema`, `asset_type`, `title`, `format`,
sdp/prd-deniable-asset-bus-2026-05-29.md:55:1. A working producer that fulfills `image` and `music` requests end-to-end against the v0.1 contract.
sdp/prd-deniable-asset-bus-2026-05-29.md:58:4. Idempotent and crash-safe: re-processing a request with an existing result is a no-op; all
sdp/prd-deniable-asset-bus-2026-05-29.md:60:5. Safe: request fields are untrusted input; no shell injection, no path traversal, bounded work.
sdp/prd-deniable-asset-bus-2026-05-29.md:65:- No requester-side code (that is the Deniable agent's job, per the frozen spec).
sdp/prd-deniable-asset-bus-2026-05-29.md:68:- No GUI, no web service, no continuous two-way mirror beyond the per-request SSH dispatch.
sdp/prd-deniable-asset-bus-2026-05-29.md:83:- **`schema.py`** — typed models for request and manifest; a `parse_request()` /
sdp/prd-deniable-asset-bus-2026-05-29.md:84:  `validate_request()` that enforces `schema == deniable-asset-bus/v0.1`, required fields, and
sdp/prd-deniable-asset-bus-2026-05-29.md:85:  `asset_type` ∈ {image, music, voiceover, sfx}. Rejects unknown/missing fields with a clear error.
sdp/prd-deniable-asset-bus-2026-05-29.md:87:  requests, atomic write (`*.tmp` + `os.replace`), `sha256` + byte size of produced files,
sdp/prd-deniable-asset-bus-2026-05-29.md:88:  result-manifest read/write, and idempotency check (result already present for a `request_id`).
sdp/prd-deniable-asset-bus-2026-05-29.md:95:- **`routers.py`** — one renderer per asset type behind a common interface; maps a validated
sdp/prd-deniable-asset-bus-2026-05-29.md:96:  request to a `BoxRunner` invocation (image → image render CLI; music → music render CLI;
sdp/prd-deniable-asset-bus-2026-05-29.md:98:- **`producer.py`** — the orchestration loop: scan `requests/`, skip already-fulfilled, validate,
sdp/prd-deniable-asset-bus-2026-05-29.md:99:  route, write produced files into `deliverables/<request_id>/`, write the manifest atomically,
sdp/prd-deniable-asset-bus-2026-05-29.md:100:  optionally update `status/`. Catches per-request errors and writes an `error` manifest rather
sdp/prd-deniable-asset-bus-2026-05-29.md:121:| DAB-001 | `promptclaw/asset_bus/schema.py` defines request and manifest models matching `docs/deniable-asset-bus-spec.md` v0.1. | MUST | T1 | Models round-trip a fixture request and manifest; field set matches the spec. |
sdp/prd-deniable-asset-bus-2026-05-29.md:122:| DAB-002 | `validate_request()` accepts conforming requests and rejects malformed ones with specific errors; unknown extra fields are ignored. | MUST | T1 | Unit tests: a valid request passes; missing `request_id`/`asset_type`/`spec`, wrong `schema`, and unknown `asset_type` each raise a distinct error; an extra field is tolerated. |
sdp/prd-deniable-asset-bus-2026-05-29.md:128:| DAB-010 | `store.py` resolves the bus root from `$DENIABLE_ASSET_BUS` (default `~/deniable-asset-bus`) and lists pending requests (those with no result manifest). | MUST | T1 | Unit test over a temp bus lists exactly the unfulfilled request ids. |
sdp/prd-deniable-asset-bus-2026-05-29.md:131:| DAB-013 | Re-processing a `request_id` that already has a result manifest is a no-op. | MUST | T1 | Idempotency test: a second pass performs no render work and does not rewrite the manifest. |
sdp/prd-deniable-asset-bus-2026-05-29.md:138:| DAB-021 | A `voiceover` request yields a `deferred` manifest with explanatory `notes` and no renderer call; the same `request_id` can be fulfilled later. | MUST | T1 | Test: a voiceover request produces status `deferred` and the fake renderer records zero calls. |
sdp/prd-deniable-asset-bus-2026-05-29.md:139:| DAB-022 | Routing dispatches each request to the renderer named by the capability matrix for its `asset_type`. | MUST | T1 | Test asserts image routes to the image renderer and music routes to the music renderer. |
sdp/prd-deniable-asset-bus-2026-05-29.md:146:| DAB-031 | `SSHBoxRunner` builds its remote command as an argv list and transfers output files back; no request-derived string is interpolated into a shell command. | MUST | T2 | Test asserts the command is constructed as an argv list and an injection fixture is passed verbatim, never via a shell string. |
sdp/prd-deniable-asset-bus-2026-05-29.md:152:| DAB-040 | `producer.py` processes all pending requests in one pass, writing one manifest per request, never aborting the batch on a single failure. | MUST | T2 | Test with a batch containing one failing request: every other request still gets a manifest. |
sdp/prd-deniable-asset-bus-2026-05-29.md:153:| DAB-041 | On renderer/runner failure write an `error` manifest with the reason; on partial success write `partial`. | MUST | T1 | Tests force failure and partial outcomes and assert the manifest status and reason. |
sdp/prd-deniable-asset-bus-2026-05-29.md:154:| DAB-042 | A continuous `run` mode polls the bus on an interval and processes newly arrived requests. | MUST | T2 | Test drives one poll iteration via an injected clock and processes a newly added request. |
sdp/prd-deniable-asset-bus-2026-05-29.md:160:| DAB-050 | `promptclaw asset-bus validate --request FILE` validates one request file and prints the normalized result or the validation error. | MUST | T1 | CLI test on valid and invalid fixtures asserts the printed output and exit code. |
sdp/prd-deniable-asset-bus-2026-05-29.md:161:| DAB-051 | `promptclaw asset-bus once` processes every pending request and writes its deliverable and manifest. | MUST | T1 | CLI test produces a manifest for each pending request in a temp bus. |
sdp/prd-deniable-asset-bus-2026-05-29.md:175:| DAB-070 | Path-bearing request fields are sanitized; produced files always land under `deliverables/<request_id>/`; path traversal and absolute paths are rejected. | MUST | T1 | Test with `../` and an absolute `target_path` is rejected; output stays inside the sandbox dir. |
sdp/prd-deniable-asset-bus-2026-05-29.md:176:| DAB-071 | Render arguments derived from request fields are passed as argv only; shell metacharacters are not interpreted. | MUST | T1 | An injection fixture in a prompt is passed literally and not interpreted. |
sdp/prd-deniable-asset-bus-2026-05-29.md:177:| DAB-072 | Bounded work: per-request ceilings on image count, music duration, and total output bytes; requests over a ceiling return `error`. | MUST | T1 | Over-limit fixtures produce an `error` manifest stating the exceeded ceiling. |
sdp/prd-deniable-asset-bus-2026-05-29.md:212:- A round-trip test: fake request → `asset-bus once` with `FakeBoxRunner` → manifest with correct
sdp/prd-deniable-asset-bus-2026-05-29.md:213:  `status`, `sha256`, and relative paths; assets present under `deliverables/<request_id>/`.
sdp/prd-deniable-asset-bus-2026-05-29.md:220:- One real `image` and one real `music` request fulfilled end-to-end against the box, results
sdp/prd-deniable-asset-bus-2026-05-29.md:227:- Request files are untrusted input. Validate strictly; never `eval`/`exec` request content.
sdp/prd-deniable-asset-bus-2026-05-29.md:228:- No shell string interpolation of request-derived values (argv only).
sdp/prd-deniable-asset-bus-2026-05-29.md:229:- All produced files confined to `deliverables/<request_id>/`; reject path traversal and absolute paths.
sdp/prd-deniable-asset-bus-2026-05-29.md:230:- Enforce per-request resource ceilings (count, duration, bytes).
sdp/prd-deniable-asset-bus-2026-05-29.md:244:- **Box availability** — if the box is unreachable, requests fail with `error`; producer must not hang.
sdp/prd-deniable-asset-bus-2026-05-29.md:249:- The Deniable agent implements the requester side per the frozen v0.1 spec.
